The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 01 October is 3,510 (406.3 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 27 September, there were 143 new confirmed cases (16.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 20 September, there were 115 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 24% (28 extra cases).
